op align=left class=m><span class=title> 4+ monsters?</span><hr size=1> I'm curious if anyone else has this problem. <br>
<br>
I'm in S. Ro.  I run around agro-ing everything with my Temp Flux staff.  Only 4 monsters chase me.  Once those 4 are dead, the others that I had hit with my staff coming running after me.  Again...only 4 of them...then, another 4 come at me...Until finally all the ones I agro'd are dead.<br>
<br>
It seems that I can't get more then 4 monsters to surround/attack me at a time.  Makes playing around with PB's on greens a bummer.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/20/01 7:43:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 4+ monsters?</span><hr size=1> *ANY* number of creatures will chase you, only 3 stop to melee with you... if more than that were chasing you, they will move off a short distance and wander... once you kill ANY of the melee'ers, one of the wanderers will now come in and take its place.<br>
<br>
The game is just set to only have 3  melee at a time. This is important when quad kiting you must keep your distance so and not give the mob a chance to melee with you... otherwise one will break off and wander.<br>
<br>
